feat(vpns): add vpn model
- Added `Vpn` model to store VPN configuration - Added `VpnService` to handle VPN operations - Updated `CustomersController` to use `VpnService` - Added `vpns` table to database

fix(vpn): add white space validations
This change adds white space validations to the VPN validator to prevent any leading or trailing whitespace in name and password fields.
BREAKING CHANGE: passwords and names can not have leading or trailing spaces

refactor: rename monitoring service to routeros service
This commit renames the `MonitoringService` to `RouterOsService` to better reflect its purpose.
The old name was misleading because it implied that the service was only responsible for monitoring traffic, when in fact it is also responsible for creating VPNs. The new name is more accurate and descriptive.
feat(router-os): add function helper to get router os instance and reconnect

feat: add websocket for monitoring traffic
This commit adds a websocket endpoint that allows for real-time monitoring of traffic on a MikroTik router.
The endpoint is located at `/monitor-traffic` and accepts a single parameter, `id`, which is the ID of the interface to monitor. The endpoint returns a stream of JSON objects, each of which contains the following data:
* `timestamp`: The time at which the data was collected * `rx_bps`: The number of bytes received per second * `tx_bps`: The number of bytes transmitted per second * `rx_pps`: The number of packets received per second * `tx_pps`: The number of packets transmitted per second
This endpoint can be used to monitor traffic on a router in real time, and to identify any potential issues.
